page.title: 12HOUSES IN 1964 AND 1982
page.content: There were 540 houses in Block 5 on the 1964 map and 572 houses in Block 6 on the 1964 map.In Block 5 in the 1982 map there are 677 houses,and in Block 6 in the 1982 map are 1,033 houses.The reason for the sudden increase in houses in Block 6 appears to be that in 1964 there were lots of fields and open rough land.This the farmers sold to developers who built houses on the land.There was little building space to put houses in Block 5 so it hasn't changed very much.The total houses on the 1964 map on both blocks was 1,061 and 1,417 on the 1982 map.
